<subSubSection id="358E8881A33E655E5ACAFEEA6ECC5B5A" pageId="15" pageNumber="510" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="7D2BDB0AA33E655E5ACAFEEA6ECC5B5A" blockId="15.[151,1437,259,610]" pageId="15" pageNumber="510">
<emphasis id="4FE00718A33E655E5ACAFEEA6D4C58B2" bold="true" box="[199,322,367,393]" pageId="15" pageNumber="510">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
A narrow-winged, dark, predominantly blackish-brown species with small tufts of raised black scales surrounded with light brown on the forewing. 
<taxonomicName id="BA94A089A33E655E58E9FE16688D5895" authority="Janse, 1958" authorityName="Janse" authorityYear="1958" box="[740,1155,403,430]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Neotelphusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="510" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anisogrisea">
<emphasis id="4FE00718A33E655E58E9FE166FF45896" box="[740,1018,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="510">Neotelphusa anisogrisea</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="1905A6FBA33E655E5E0DFE11688D5895" author="Janse, A. J. T." box="[1024,1155,403,430]" pageId="15" pageNumber="510" pagination="1 - 144" refId="ref15108" refString="Janse, A. J. T. (1958) Gelechiidae. The Moths of South Africa, 6 (1), 1 - 144, pls. 1 - 32." type="journal article" year="1958">Janse, 1958</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="BA94A089A33E655E5EB5FE116CC158E9" authority="Janse, 1958" authorityName="Janse" authorityYear="1958" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Neotelphusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="510" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavinotata">
<emphasis id="4FE00718A33E655E5EB5FE11695C5896" box="[1208,1362,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="510">N. flavinotata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="1905A6FBA33E655E5F54FE116CC158E9" author="Janse, A. J. T." pageId="15" pageNumber="510" pagination="1 - 144" refId="ref15108" refString="Janse, A. J. T. (1958) Gelechiidae. The Moths of South Africa, 6 (1), 1 - 144, pls. 1 - 32." type="journal article" year="1958">Janse, 1958</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
have a similar wing pattern but the ground colour of the forewing is lighter, greyish brown rather than blackish brown, and the light brown surrounding of the tufts of black raised scales is more extensive. The male genitalia can easily be recognized by the broad uncus and gnathos which are unique for species of 
<taxonomicName id="BA94A089A33E655E5E46FD8569595B22" authority="Meyrick, 1918" authorityName="Meyrick" authorityYear="1918" box="[1099,1367,511,537]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Istrianis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="510" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4FE00718A33E655E5E46FD8568A65B22" box="[1099,1192,512,537]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="510">Istrianis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="1905A6FBA33E655E5EA2FE7A69595B22" author="Meyrick, E." box="[1199,1367,511,537]" pageId="15" pageNumber="510" pagination="7 - 59" refId="ref15788" refString="Meyrick, E. (1918) Descriptions of South African Micro-Lepidoptera. Annals of the Transvaal Museum, 6 (2), 7 - 59." type="journal article" year="1918">Meyrick, 1918</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Wide drop-shaped subostial anterior sclerites, distinct subostial folds, lack of posterior sclerite in combination with large signum are characteristic for the female genitalia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
