<emphasis id="4FE00718A33E655E5ACAF8F06DAB5EB4" bold="true" box="[199,421,1909,1935]" pageId="15" pageNumber="510">Description. Adult</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="E5AFC78FA33E655E5BBAF8F06E325EAB" box="[439,572,1909,1936]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–28" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1766,1790]" captionTargetBox="[178,1412,648,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-184@15.[161,1426,633,1742]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 23–28. Istrianis spp., adults. 23–25. I. inquilinus sp. nov. 23. Holotype. 24. Paratype, male (gen. slide 163/19, O. Bidzilya). 25. Paratype, female (gen. slide 152/19, O. Bidzilya). 26–28. I. epacria. 26. Holotype. 27. Kenya, male (gen. slide 1443, O. Bidzilya). 28. Kenya, female (gen. slide 1444, O. Bidzilya)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690587" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690587/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="510">Figs 23–25</figureCitation>
). Wingspan 11.4–13.0 mm. 
<emphasis id="4FE00718A33E655E598CF8F06FB05EB4" box="[897,958,1909,1935]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="510">Head</emphasis>
covered with grey, apically brown scales with grey tips, frons lighter, white to light grey laterally mixed with black, labial palpus upcurved, palpomere 2 covered with black white-tipped scales with very narrow diffuse white medial ring on outer surface, inner and upper surface slightly lighter, black to brown densely mottled with white, palpomere 3 white with broad black medial and subapical rings, scape black mottled with white especially underside, flagellomeres black with narrowly brownringed at base, densely white ciliate ventrally in male. 
<emphasis id="4FE00718A32165415908FF3E6F5859EE" box="[773,854,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="511">Thorax</emphasis>
and tegula colored as head, forewing covered with blackish-brown white-tipped scales, costal margin suffused with black to 1/ 
<quantity id="BA6C76EFA321654159E0FF5A681759C2" box="[1005,1049,223,249]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.62" pageId="16" pageNumber="511" unit="in" value="3.0">3 in</quantity>
male, diffuse tufts of black scales at basal 1/ 
<quantity id="BA6C76EFA32165415B04FE866D3B5826" box="[265,309,259,285]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.524" pageId="16" pageNumber="511" unit="in" value="6.0">6 in</quantity>
mid width and at 1/ 
<quantity id="BA6C76EFA32165415815FE876E4A5826" box="[536,580,258,285]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.27" pageId="16" pageNumber="511" unit="in" value="5.0">5 in</quantity>
fold, black touch edged dorsally with light brown at end of fold near dorsal margin, four small tufts of black raised scales surrounded with light brown at 1/3 under costal margin, in mid width at 1/2 length, and at 2/3 near dorsum and in mid width, cilia black, grey-tipped, hindwing and cilia light grey. Male with subcostal pocket with pencil of light brown hairs from base to 1/3. 
<emphasis id="4FE00718A321654159B1FEEA682858B2" box="[956,1062,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="511">Abdomen</emphasis>
grey, terga VIII in male (
<figureCitation id="E5AFC78FA32165415F4CFEEA6CBA5896" captionStart="FIGURES 29–35" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1891,1915]" captionTargetBox="[243,1392,231,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-18@18.[170,1416,181,1868]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 29–35. Istrianis spp. 29–32. Male genitalia. 29, 30. I. inquilinus sp. nov. 29. Holotype. 30. Paratype (gen. slide 39/15, O. Bidzilya). 31, 32. I. epacria. 31. Holotype (gen. slide 8717, NHM). 32. Kenya (gen. slide 1443, O. Bidzilya). 33–35. Male abdominal segments. 33, 34. I. inquilinus sp. nov. 33. Terga VIII, holotype. 34. Segment VIII, paratype (gen. slide 39/15, O. Bidzilya). 35. I. epacria, segment VIII, Kenya (gen. slide 1443, O. Bidzilya)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690589" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690589/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="511">Figs 33, 34</figureCitation>
) sub-triangular, rounded posteriorly, posterior portion from triangular to tongue-shaped, anteromedial emargination reverse V-shaped, extending to 1/2 length of sternum VIII; basal coremata composed of long dense tuft of hairlike scales, extending to about 2/3 length of terga; sternum VIII (
<figureCitation id="E5AFC78FA3216541596AFE5E6FB658CE" box="[871,952,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–35" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1891,1915]" captionTargetBox="[243,1392,231,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-18@18.[170,1416,181,1868]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 29–35. Istrianis spp. 29–32. Male genitalia. 29, 30. I. inquilinus sp. nov. 29. Holotype. 30. Paratype (gen. slide 39/15, O. Bidzilya). 31, 32. I. epacria. 31. Holotype (gen. slide 8717, NHM). 32. Kenya (gen. slide 1443, O. Bidzilya). 33–35. Male abdominal segments. 33, 34. I. inquilinus sp. nov. 33. Terga VIII, holotype. 34. Segment VIII, paratype (gen. slide 39/15, O. Bidzilya). 35. I. epacria, segment VIII, Kenya (gen. slide 1443, O. Bidzilya)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690589" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690589/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="511">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
) about 2.5 times as broad as long, posterior margin weakly rounded, covered with dense hairs, posteriolateral corners extending in short rounded projections covered apically with short hairs. 
<emphasis id="4FE00718A32165415800FDA66EB85B07" bold="true" box="[525,694,546,573]" pageId="16" pageNumber="511">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="E5AFC78FA321654158C9FDA66F4F5B06" box="[708,833,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–35" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1891,1915]" captionTargetBox="[243,1392,231,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-18@18.[170,1416,181,1868]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 29–35. Istrianis spp. 29–32. Male genitalia. 29, 30. I. inquilinus sp. nov. 29. Holotype. 30. Paratype (gen. slide 39/15, O. Bidzilya). 31, 32. I. epacria. 31. Holotype (gen. slide 8717, NHM). 32. Kenya (gen. slide 1443, O. Bidzilya). 33–35. Male abdominal segments. 33, 34. I. inquilinus sp. nov. 33. Terga VIII, holotype. 34. Segment VIII, paratype (gen. slide 39/15, O. Bidzilya). 35. I. epacria, segment VIII, Kenya (gen. slide 1443, O. Bidzilya)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690589" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690589/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="511">Figs 29, 30</figureCitation>
) with uncus roughly parallel-sided in distal half, twice as long as broad, posterior margin broadly rounded and strongly edged, posterolateral corners distinct; gnathos slightly shorter than uncus, broad at base, gradually constricted to mid length, posterior margin and posterolateral corners strongly sclerotized; tegumen twice as broad as long, lateral lobes broad, rounded anteriorly, anteromedial emargination shallow, sub-triangular; valva narrow, about 1/3 length of phallus; vinculum narrow, band-shaped; phallus twice as long as broad, distal 1/3 triangular, tapered apically into pointed tip, ductus ejaculatorius very long with coiled lamina. 
<emphasis id="4FE00718A32165415B75FD7E6E335A2F" bold="true" box="[376,573,762,789]" pageId="16" pageNumber="511">Female genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="E5AFC78FA32165415840FD7E6EDF5A2E" box="[589,721,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURES 36–39" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[174,1363,197,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-16@19.[151,1435,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 36–39. Istrianis spp., female genitalia. 36, 37. I. inquilinus sp. nov. 36. Paratype (gen. slide 152/19, O. Bidzilya). 37. Paratype (gen. slide 43/15, O. Bidzilya). 38, 39. I. epacria. 38. Paratype (gen. slide 9616, NHM). 39. Kenya (gen. slide 1444, O. Bidzilya)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690591" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690591/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="511">Figs 36, 37</figureCitation>
). Papillae anales subovate, covered with short setae; apophyses posteriores 2.5-3 times as long as apophyses anteriores; segment VII about as long as broad, antrum bowl-shaped, posterior sclerite absent, anterior sclerites drop-shaped, subostial folds distinct, strongly sclerotized; ductus bursae slightly longer than apophyses posteriores, weakly broadened towards corpus bursae; corpus bursae egg-shaped, about twice as long as broad; signum a subrhomboid plate with serrated margins and narrow medial ridge, anterior lobe broader than posterior lobe, about as broad as width of corpus bursae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="358E8881A32165415ACAFC576ED85D2A" pageId="16" pageNumber="511" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="7D2BDB0AA32165415ACAFC576ED85D2A" blockId="16.[151,1437,151,1221]" pageId="16" pageNumber="511">
<emphasis id="4FE00718A32165415ACAFC576D295AD7" bold="true" box="[199,295,978,1004]" pageId="16" pageNumber="511">Biology.</emphasis>
The larvae were bred from flower galls produced by the fungus 
<taxonomicName id="BA94A089A32165415E03FC5669095AD5" authority="(Puccinalis)" baseAuthorityName="Puccinalis" box="[1038,1287,979,1006]" class="Pucciniomycetes" genus="Aecidium" kingdom="Chromista" order="Pucciniales" pageId="16" pageNumber="511" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4FE00718A32165415E03FC5668765AD6" box="[1038,1144,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="511">Aecidium</emphasis>
(Puccinalis)
</taxonomicName>
on 
<taxonomicName id="BA94A089A32165415F39FC566CEC5D2A" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Vachellia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="16" pageNumber="511" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="karroo">
<emphasis id="4FE00718A32165415F39FC566CEC5D2A" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="511">Vachellia karroo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="BA94A089A32165415AFCFC726D6E5D29" box="[241,352,1015,1042]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="16" pageNumber="511" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Fabaceae</taxonomicName>
). Adults emerged in early March.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="358E8881A32165415ACAFB9F6EFA5D0E" box="[199,756,1050,1077]" pageId="16" pageNumber="511" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="7D2BDB0AA32165415ACAFB9F6EFA5D0E" blockId="16.[151,1437,151,1221]" box="[199,756,1050,1077]" pageId="16" pageNumber="511">
<emphasis id="4FE00718A32165415ACAFB9F6D6F5D0F" bold="true" box="[199,353,1050,1076]" pageId="16" pageNumber="511">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="05839B9AA32165415B6AFB9E6DF45D0E" box="[359,506,1051,1077]" name="South Africa" pageId="16" pageNumber="511">South Africa</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion id="BF5015E8A32165415808FB9E6EFF5D0E" box="[517,753,1051,1077]" country="South Africa" name="North West" pageId="16" pageNumber="511">North West province</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="358E8881A32165415ACAFBBA69255D62" box="[199,1323,1087,1113]" pageId="16" pageNumber="511" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="7D2BDB0AA32165415ACAFBBA69255D62" blockId="16.[151,1437,151,1221]" box="[199,1323,1087,1113]" pageId="16" pageNumber="511">
<emphasis id="4FE00718A32165415ACAFBBA6D405D62" bold="true" box="[199,334,1087,1113]" pageId="16" pageNumber="511">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name refers to the larvae living inside galls produced by another organism.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="358E8881A32165415ACAFBE66F2D5DFE" pageId="16" pageNumber="511" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="7D2BDB0AA32165415ACAFBE66F2D5DFE" blockId="16.[151,1437,151,1221]" pageId="16" pageNumber="511">
<emphasis id="4FE00718A32165415ACAFBE66D355D46" bold="true" box="[199,315,1123,1149]" pageId="16" pageNumber="511">Remarks.</emphasis>
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="BA94A089A32165415BC8FBE66EDD5D46" authority="Meyrick, 1918" authorityName="Meyrick" authorityYear="1918" box="[453,723,1123,1149]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Istrianis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="511" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4FE00718A32165415BC8FBE66E2C5D47" box="[453,546,1123,1148]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="511">Istrianis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="1905A6FBA32165415821FBE66EDD5D46" author="Meyrick, E." box="[556,723,1123,1149]" pageId="16" pageNumber="511" pagination="7 - 59" refId="ref15788" refString="Meyrick, E. (1918) Descriptions of South African Micro-Lepidoptera. Annals of the Transvaal Museum, 6 (2), 7 - 59." type="journal article" year="1918">Meyrick, 1918</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
comprises 22 species (
<bibRefCitation id="1905A6FBA321654159EDFBE669015D46" author="Bidzilya, O. &amp; Karsholt, O." box="[992,1295,1122,1149]" pageId="16" pageNumber="511" pagination="401 - 445" refId="ref14308" refString="Bidzilya, O. &amp; Karsholt, O. (2015) Revision of the genus Istrianis Meyrick, 1918 (Lepidoptera, Gelechiidae) with special regard to the Palaearctic region. Zootaxa, 4059 (3), 401 - 445. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4059.3.1" type="journal article" year="2015">Bidzilya &amp; Karsholt 2015</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="1905A6FBA32165415F13FBE66D435D9A" author="Bidzilya, O. &amp; Nupponen, K." pageId="16" pageNumber="511" pagination="381 - 408" refId="ref14421" refString="Bidzilya, O. &amp; Nupponen, K. (2018) New species and new records of gelechiid moths (Lepidoptera, Gelechiidae) from southern Siberia. Zootaxa, 4444 (4), 381 - 408. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4444.4.2" type="journal article" year="2018">Bidzilya &amp; Nupponen 2018</bibRefCitation>
) of which one is known from 
<collectingCountry id="05839B9AA321654158ADFB026F3C5D9A" box="[672,818,1159,1185]" name="South Africa" pageId="16" pageNumber="511">South Africa</collectingCountry>
. However, many South African species of 
<taxonomicName id="BA94A089A32165415F1DFB026D145DFE" authority="Janse, 1958" authorityName="Janse" authorityYear="1958" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Neotelphusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="511" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4FE00718A32165415F1DFB0269925D9A" box="[1296,1436,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="511">Neotelphusa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="1905A6FBA32165415A9AFB2E6D145DFE" author="Janse, A. J. T." box="[151,282,1194,1221]" pageId="16" pageNumber="511" pagination="1 - 144" refId="ref15108" refString="Janse, A. J. T. (1958) Gelechiidae. The Moths of South Africa, 6 (1), 1 - 144, pls. 1 - 32." type="journal article" year="1958">Janse, 1958</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
belongs in fact to 
<taxonomicName id="BA94A089A32165415BE4FB2E6E485DFF" authorityName="Meyrick" authorityYear="1918" box="[489,582,1195,1220]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Istrianis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="511" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4FE00718A32165415BE4FB2E6E485DFF" box="[489,582,1195,1220]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="511">Istrianis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Bidzilya in prep.).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
